<Layout title="Terms of Service - Sojorn" description="Sojorn Terms of Service">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2 text-egyptianBlue">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-gray-500">Last Updated: February 21, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none text-gray-700">
      <p class="lead font-semibold">By using Sojorn ("the Service"), you agree to these Terms of Service ("Terms"), which constitute a binding agreement between you and MPLS LLC ("we," "us," "our").</p>

      <!-- ─── 1. ELIGIBILITY ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">1. Eligibility</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">You must be at least 18 years of age to use Sojorn. By creating an account, you represent and warrant that you are at least 18 years old. We do not use age verification technology such as ID scanning or biometric checks. However, if we become aware that a user has misrepresented their age and is under 18 — whether through self-disclosure, reports, or other means — we will immediately delete their account and all associated data without prior notice.</p>

      <!-- ─── 2. YOUR ACCOUNT ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">2. Your Account</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account credentials. You must provide a valid email address and may not impersonate another person or use a misleading handle. We reserve the right to reclaim handles that are inactive, misleading, or reserved for platform use. One person, one account — operating multiple accounts to evade moderation or manipulate the platform is prohibited.</p>

      <!-- ─── 3. COMMUNITY STANDARDS ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">3. Community Standards</h2>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-4 mb-2">3.1 Zero Tolerance</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">Hate speech, racism, sexism, homophobia, transphobia, ableism, and fascist ideologies are strictly prohibited. Violations result in immediate and permanent account suspension.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-4 mb-2">3.2 No Misinformation</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">Posting verifiable falsehoods, conspiracy theories, or coordinated disinformation with intent to deceive is prohibited and will result in content removal and potential account termination.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-4 mb-2">3.3 No Harassment</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">Targeted harassment, doxxing, threats, stalking, and coordinated pile-on behavior are prohibited. This includes using Beacons or neighborhood boards to target, surveil, or endanger individuals.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-4 mb-2">3.4 No Spam or Manipulation</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">Automated posting, engagement farming, coordinated inauthentic behavior, and commercial spam are prohibited.</p>

      <!-- ─── 4. CONTENT OWNERSHIP ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">4. Content Ownership</h2>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-4 mb-2">4.1 Your Rights</h3>
      <p class="mb-4"><strong>You retain 100% copyright and all intellectual property rights</strong> to every piece of content you create on Sojorn. We claim no ownership over your words, images, audio, video, or any other creative work.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-4 mb-2">4.2 Limited Technical License</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">By posting content, you grant MPLS LLC a <strong>non-exclusive, royalty-free, worldwide license solely for the technical purpose of hosting, displaying, and transmitting your content</strong> to the audience you designate within Sojorn. This license covers necessary operations such as image resizing, video transcoding, thumbnail generation, and content delivery.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-4 mb-2">4.3 Immediate Revocation</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">This technical license <strong>expires immediately and irrevocably upon deletion</strong> of the content by you. We do not retain shadow copies, hidden archives, or soft-deleted records. Residual copies in disaster-recovery backups are purged within 14 days.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-4 mb-2">4.4 Anti-Extraction Covenant</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">MPLS LLC <strong>will never</strong> use your content to train AI models, sell your content or data to third parties, export your engagement data outside of Sojorn, or index your content on public search engines without your explicit opt-in.</p>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mt-4 mb-2">4.5 Right to Livelihood</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">If MPLS LLC ever wishes to use your content for promotional purposes, we must contact you directly, offer financial compensation, and receive your explicit written consent. No blanket consent is granted by agreeing to these Terms.</p>

      <!-- ─── 5. COMMUNITY SAFETY BEACONS ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">5. Community Safety Beacons</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sojorn includes a community safety feature ("Beacons") that allows users to report real-world safety situations with approximate location data. By using Beacons, you agree to the following:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Good faith reporting</strong> — Beacons must describe genuine safety situations. Posting false safety alerts to cause panic, harass individuals, or disrupt communities is a serious violation and will result in immediate account termination.</li>
        <li><strong>No targeting individuals</strong> — Beacons are for community safety awareness, not for tracking, surveilling, or targeting specific people. Using Beacons to report on individuals' movements, locations, or activities is prohibited.</li>
        <li><strong>Location imprecision</strong> — Beacon and board locations are automatically reduced in precision (~1.1 km) before storage. You should not include precise addresses or identifying location details in beacon text.</li>
        <li><strong>Neutral language</strong> — Beacon text is automatically processed through a neutral-language filter. Specific agency names and enforcement terminology are replaced with general terms for community safety and App Store compliance.</li>
        <li><strong>Community verification</strong> — Other users can vote on beacon credibility. Low-confidence beacons may be de-prioritized or removed.</li>
        <li><strong>No guarantee of accuracy</strong> — Sojorn does not verify the accuracy of beacon reports. Beacons represent user-submitted information and should not be relied upon as the sole source of safety information. Always follow guidance from official emergency services.</li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ─── 6. NEIGHBORHOOD BOARDS ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">6. Neighborhood Boards</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Neighborhood boards are local community spaces tied to geographic areas. Board entries are visible to users in the relevant area. The same community standards (Section 3) apply to board content. Board entries include approximate location data (reduced to ~1.1 km precision). Board topics are limited to: community, question, event, lost pet, resource, recommendation, and warning.</p>

      <!-- ─── 7. GROUPS & CAPSULES ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">7. Groups &amp; Encrypted Capsules</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sojorn offers groups for community organizing, with optional end-to-end encryption ("Capsules") for sensitive conversations. Group owners and admins are responsible for moderation within their groups. Groups that systematically violate community standards may be deactivated by Sojorn administrators.</p>
      <p class="mb-4">Encrypted Capsule content is end-to-end encrypted and cannot be read by Sojorn. However, metadata (group membership, message timestamps, group names) is visible to us and subject to moderation if the group itself violates our Terms.</p>

      <!-- ─── 8. END-TO-END ENCRYPTION ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">8. End-to-End Encryption</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Private messages and encrypted Capsule content are protected by end-to-end encryption (E2EE) using keys generated on your device. MPLS LLC has no ability to decrypt, read, or access this content. You are responsible for safeguarding your encryption keys. If you lose your keys and have not set up social recovery, your encrypted message history cannot be recovered — by you or by us.</p>

      <!-- ─── 9. AI MODERATION ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">9. AI Moderation</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We use artificial intelligence to assist with content moderation of public content. AI moderation:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Operates only on public content (posts, comments, board entries) — never on private encrypted messages or Capsule content</li>
        <li>May flag content for human review, apply NSFW labels, or remove content that violates community standards</li>
        <li>Produces a moderation log including AI scores and a content snippet retained for 14 days to support appeals</li>
        <li>Is subject to human review — you may appeal any AI moderation decision through the in-app appeal process</li>
        <li>Is not perfect — false positives happen, which is why the appeal process exists</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">Moderation actions are logged for transparency. When content is removed by AI or human moderators, you will be notified with the reason for removal.</p>

      <!-- ─── 10. TRUST & RATE LIMITING ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">10. Trust &amp; Rate Limiting</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sojorn uses an internal trust system ("harmony score") to manage platform health. Your harmony score is influenced by community standing, moderation history, and posting patterns. Users with lower trust scores may experience rate limiting on certain actions (posting, commenting, beacon creation). Your harmony score is not visible to other users or advertisers.</p>

      <!-- ─── 11. ADVERTISING ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">11. Advertising</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sojorn may display clearly labeled sponsored content ("Sponsored" or "Promoted") to fund platform operations. All advertising is served in-house by MPLS LLC. Ad relevance is determined by your geographic neighborhood, content section, interest categories you declare, and your in-app engagement (such as likes and saves). This data is never shared with advertisers or any third party. You can disable engagement-based ad relevance in your settings.</p>
      <p class="mb-4">Sponsored content is held to the same community guidelines and AI moderation standards as all other content. No exceptions are made for paying advertisers. Users may hide or dismiss individual sponsored posts. Full details are available in our <a href="/advertising" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">Advertising Policy</a>.</p>

      <!-- ─── 12. YOUR RIGHT TO VANISH ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">12. Your Right to Vanish</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">You have the absolute right to delete your account and all associated data at any time. When you leave, you leave. We perform hard deletes — your profile, posts, comments, media files, encryption keys, moderation records, and all metadata are permanently removed from our systems. Disaster-recovery backups containing your data are purged within 14 days. You can delete your account through the app or via our <a href="/settings/delete-account" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">account deletion form</a>.</p>

      <!-- ─── 13. ENFORCEMENT & APPEALS ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">13. Enforcement &amp; Appeals</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Violations of these Terms may result in:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Content removal</strong> — individual posts, comments, or beacons removed with notification</li>
        <li><strong>Soft violation</strong> — warning and temporary restrictions</li>
        <li><strong>Hard violation</strong> — account suspension (temporary or permanent)</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">All enforcement actions can be appealed through the in-app appeal system. Appeals are reviewed by a human moderator. If your appeal is upheld, the action is reversed and the violation is removed from your record.</p>

      <!-- ─── 14. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">14. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">The Sojorn name, logo, and branding are trademarks of MPLS LLC. The Sojorn platform software is publicly available under a split licensing model. For full details, see our <a href="/licenses" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">Licenses</a> page. The complete source code is available at <a href="https://gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn</a>.</p>

      <!-- ─── 15. DISCLAIMERS ─── -->
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">15. Disclaimers &amp; Limitations</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">MPLS LLC provides the Service "as is" and "as available." We make no warranties regarding uptime, accuracy of user-generated content (including Beacons), or fitness for a particular purpose. Specifically:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Beacon and safety alerts are user-generated and unverified. Do not rely on them as your sole safety information source.</li>
        <li>End-to-end encryption depends on the security of your device. We are not responsible for key loss or device compromise.</li>
        <li>We are not liable for interactions between users, though we commit to active moderation.</li>
        <li>Third-party safety data displayed in the app is sourced from external APIs and may be inaccurate or delayed.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">To the maximum extent permitted by law, MPLS LLC's total liability for any claim arising from your use of the Service is limited to the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim (if any).</p>

